FBIS4-61102 "drsov086_f_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-086 Daily Report 2 May 1994 National Affairs Ministers Lead Commission Investigating Mine Accident Ministers Lead Commission Investigating Mine Accident LD0205165294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1620 GMT 2 May 94 LD0205165294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [Report by correspondent ITAR-TASS Anatoliy Gordeyev] [Text] Makeyevka (Donetsk Oblast), 2 May--According to preliminary reports, 12 miners died today at the Sovetskaya mine of the Makeyevugol production association, when a methane explosion occurred during the first shift. The cause of the accident is being investigated. A government commission headed by Deputy Prime Minister Vasyl Yevtukhov has arrived at the site of the tragedy. Acting Ukrainian Prime Minister Yefim Zvyahilskyy has also arrived in Makeyevka.
